50|$|Erucastrum gallicum is {{an annual}} or {{biennial}} {{plant in the}} mustard family known by the common names <b>hairy</b> <b>rocket</b> and common dogmustard. It is a weedy plant with an erect upright habit or sometimes with ascending tops with bright yellow flowers. Plants bloom in late spring through the summer into early autumn. As plants bloom the stems extend upward and when finished blooming plants are 30 to 60 centimeters long. The plant is native to Eurasia but is an introduced species {{in many areas of}} the world, including much of North America.|$|E

